  "text": "Kidson-Gerber et al. draw attention to the importance of attentive postdelivery care, with frequent evaluation of the patient's general condition and uterine fundus. They emphasize the need for systematic postdelivery blood loss control, which aids in recognizing persistent loss of small blood volumes, eventually resulting in significant deficiency [CITATION_1] .",
